AGI -&nbsp; A lonely navigator dispersed for a few days between Greece is Italy was rescued by the Coast Guard off Roccella Jonica, in an operation that ended at dawn. The man, of Spanish nationality, had begun on 11 April a navigation from the island of Crete to Sicily, aboard a sailing boat of 12 meters.
&nbsp;
After receiving the information from the rescue center of the Athenian port of Piraeus and acquired a satellite signal that indicated the possible presence of the unit 110 miles from Capo Spartivento, about 200 kilometers from the coast of Calabria, the rescue machine of the Coast Guard was set up coordinated by the Maritime Direction of Reggio Calabria, with an airplane removed from Catania, a motorvedetta game from Roccella Jonica and two merchants. With poor weather conditions >, 40 knots of wind and sea 5 worsening, it was finally spotted by the aircraft of the Guard Costiera the "Black Bit", with its skipper throwing light signals > to be spotted. The yacht was reached in the heart of the night by the motorboat CP311 of Roccella Jonica that took on board the sailor. After the first care on the Coast Guard unit, the Spanish was entrusted to the health care of the 118 on arrival at the port of Roccella this morning.&nbsp;
